@ThomasVitale - I got this working for a non-streaming response. But for a scenario where I want to stream the response, retrieving the documents is resulting in an error. 
My use case is to stream the response, and then after the chat content is streamed, pass the file names (for citation purposes) to the client. 

Something like this -

```
StreamResponseSpec spec = chatClient.prompt().user(userMessage).advisors(a -> {
            a.param(CHAT_MEMORY_CONVERSATION_ID_KEY, chatId);
            a.param(CHAT_MEMORY_RETRIEVE_SIZE_KEY, 20);
        }).advisors(RetrievalAugmentationAdvisor.builder()
                .queryTransformers(
                        CompressionQueryTransformer.builder()
                                .chatClientBuilder(builder.build().mutate()).build(),
                        RewriteQueryTransformer.builder()
                                .chatClientBuilder(builder.build().mutate()).build())
                .documentRetriever(VectorStoreDocumentRetriever.builder().vectorStore(vectorStore)
                        .similarityThreshold(0.5).topK(10).build())
                .queryAugmenter(ContextualQueryAugmenter.builder().allowEmptyContext(false)
                        .promptTemplate(new PromptTemplate(CONTEXT_PROMPT)).build())
                .build()).stream();


         // Get the content as a Flux<String>
        Flux<String> contentFlux = spec.content();

        // Get the first ChatClientResponse, extract documents, and emit citations
        Flux<String> citationsFlux = spec.chatClientResponse().take(1).flatMap(response -> {
            Object docsObj = response.context().get(RetrievalAugmentationAdvisor.DOCUMENT_CONTEXT);
            if (docsObj instanceof List<?> docsList && !docsList.isEmpty()
                    && docsList.get(0) instanceof Document) {
                @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
                List<Document> documents = (List<Document>) docsObj;
                Set<String> fileNames = retrieveFileNames(documents);
                return Flux.just("Citations: " + fileNames);
            } else {
                logger.warn("DOCUMENT_CONTEXT is not a List<Document>: {}", docsObj);
            }
            return Flux.empty();
        }).onErrorResume(e -> {
            logger.error("Error extracting citations", e);
            return Flux.empty();
        });


        // Concatenate the content and citations
        return contentFlux.concatWith(citationsFlux);
```

But this is resulting in an error as follows -

```
java.lang.IllegalStateException: No StreamAdvisors available to execute
	at org.springframework.ai.chat.client.advisor.DefaultAroundAdvisorChain.lambda$nextStream$10(DefaultAroundAdvisorChain.java:173) ~[spring-ai-client-chat-1.0.0-M8.jar:1.0.0-M8]
	at reactor.core.publisher.FluxDeferContextual.subscribe(FluxDeferContextual.java:49) ~[reactor-core-3.7.5.jar:3.7.5]
	at reactor.core.publisher.InternalFluxOperator.subscribe(InternalFluxOperator.java:68) ~[reactor-core-3.7.5.jar:3.7.5]
	at reactor.core.publisher.FluxDeferContextual.subscribe(FluxDeferContextual.java:57) ~[reactor-core-3.7.5.jar:3.7.5]
	at reactor.core.publisher.Flux.subscribe(Flux.java:8891) ~[reactor-core-3.7.5.jar:3.7.5]
```

How can I manage to retrieve the documents for this use case?
